    <briefdescription>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>An input context contains all keybindings and actions active in e.g. the HUD only. For the console, there&apos;s a different input context. That way, each context can have the same keys assigned to different actions, the active context decides, which one to trigger. </para>
    </detaileddescription>
